  "title": "2025 Edition",
  "subtitle": "My top X of 2025 in no particular order",
  "sections": [
    {
      "name": "Games",
      "icon": "🎮",
      "status": "Now playing",
      "url": "https://backloggd.com/u/BananaDaemon/",
      "items": [
        {
          "title": "Clair Obscur: Expedition 33",
          "note": "The prologue and first act story/world building were really good. I felt it was weird how they dumped all the side stuff to act 3, which caused pacing to be weird. I feel this is a good step for turn based RPGs and hopefully will make the next games learn from it. For those who come after.",
          "image": "https://images.igdb.com/igdb/image/upload/t_cover_big_2x/co9gam.jpg",
          "redirect": "https://backloggd.com/games/clair-obscur-expedition-33/"
        },
        {
          "title": "Hollow Knight: Silksong",
          "note": " Metroidvania at it's finest, the multiple paths to reach the same area and how you are never sure if you're doing a cheesy strat or if it's the intended route was fun. Gaunlet fights are annoying as hell, and fuck Bilewater.",
          "image": "https://images.igdb.com/igdb/image/upload/t_cover_big_2x/cobebu.jpg",
          "redirect": "https://backloggd.com/games/hollow-knight-silksong/"
        },
        {
          "title": "Blue Prince",
          "note": "Took over my life for a week. The pacing can be a bit all over due to the nature of the randomness. The best part was playing it while everyone else was still playing and talking to people about it. ",
          "image": "https://images.igdb.com/igdb/image/upload/t_cover_big_2x/co9mzd.jpg",
          "redirect": "https://backloggd.com/games/blue-prince/"
        },
        {
          "title": "Death Stranding 2: On the Beach",
          "note": "Kojima being kojima, the game makes absolutely no sense and there shouldn't be a reason why I enjoyed it so much. The plot is nonsense and you're just there for the weird vibes. The game became a bit too combat focused for my liking, but the idea of building a network and seeing how the community comes together to make the game easier was really good (Not a new idea since Death Stranding 1 already did it but still I enjoyed it)",
          "image": "https://images.igdb.com/igdb/image/upload/t_cover_big_2x/co9ipx.jpg",
          "redirect": "https://backloggd.com/games/death-stranding-2-on-the-beach/"
        },
        {
          "title": "Football Manager 2024",
          "note": "Management games just hook you up, learned more about soccer strats, both in and out of the pitch. Not much to say about it besides an excelent waste of time. Maybe in another life instead of FM24 I would have been hooked up on Uma Musume. ",
          "image": "https://images.igdb.com/igdb/image/upload/t_cover_big_2x/co73z1.jpg",
          "redirect": "https://backloggd.com/games/football-manager-2024/"
        }
      ]
    },
